\subsection{Dirichlet group of an Abelian number field}
\begin{definition}\label{nf.dirichlet_group}
\uses{character.dirichlet,nf.abelian,nf.conductor}
If $K$ is an {{ KNOWL('nf.abelian', 'abelian number field') }}, then $K\subseteq \Q(\zeta_n)$ for some positive integer $n$.  Take the minimal such $n$, i.e., the {{ KNOWL('nf.conductor', 'conductor') }} of $K$.

The Galois group $\Gal(\Q(\zeta_n)/\Q)$ is canonically isomorphic to $\Z_n^\times$.  The {{ KNOWL('character.dirichlet', 'Dirichlet characters') }} modulo $n$ form the dual group of homomorphisms $\chi:\Z_n^\times\to\C^\times$.  Since $\Gal(K/\Q)$ is a quotient group of $\Gal(\Q(\zeta_n)/\Q)$, its dual group is a subgroup of the group of Dirichlet characters modulo $n$, called the **Dirichlet character group** of $K$.
\end{definition}


